[468.914888, "o", "\u001b[4mKILL\u001b[24m(1)                    User Commands                    \u001b[4mKILL\u001b[24m(1)\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mNAME\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       kill - send a signal to a process\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mSYNOPSIS\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mkill \u001b[22m[options] <pid> [...]\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mDESCRIPTION\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       The  default  signal for kill is TERM.  Use \u001b[1m-l \u001b[22mor \u001b[1m-L \u001b[22mto list\u001b[m\r\n       available signals.  Particularly useful signals include HUP,\u001b[m\r\n       INT, KILL, STOP, CONT, and  0.   Alternate  signals  may  be\u001b[m\r\n       specified  in  three  ways: \u001b[1m-9\u001b[22m, \u001b[1m-SIGKILL \u001b[22mor \u001b[1m-KILL\u001b[22m.  Negative\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page kill(1) line 1 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[472.915255, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       PID values may be used to choose whole process  groups;  see\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page kill(1) line 2 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[473.393561, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       the  PGID  column in ps command output.  A PID of \u001b[1m-1 \u001b[22mis spe‐\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page kill(1) line 3 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[473.896176, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       cial; it indicates all processes except the kill process it‐\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page kill(1) line 4 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[473.930422, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       self and init.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page kill(1) line 5 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
